{"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. As such, we often need to deprecate certain APIs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in favor of newer ones. We recommend people update their code as quickly as possible to the newest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"APIs, and this article contains some tips for doing so."}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Sending test store actions","anchor":"Sending-test-store-actions"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Version 1.4 of the library introduced the ability to receive test store actions using case key path","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"syntax, massively simplifying how one asserts on actions received in a test:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["-store.receive(.child(.presented(.response(.success(\"Hello\")))))","+store.receive(\\.child.response.success)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While version 1.6 of the library introduced the ability to assert against the payload of a received"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"action:"}]},{"code":["store.receive(\\.child.presented.success, \"Hello\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.9 introduces similar affordances for "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"sending","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" actions to test stores via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TestStore\/send(_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)-8877x"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore\/send(_:_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)"},{"type":"text","text":". These methods can significantly simplify"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"integration-style tests that send deeply-nested actions to child features, and provide symmetry to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"how actions are received:"}]},{"code":["-store.send(.path(.element(id: 0, action: .destination(.presented(.record(.startButtonTapped))))))","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].destination.record.startButtonTapped)"," store.receive(\\.path[id: 0].destination.record.timerTick)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Case key paths offer specialized syntax for many different action types."}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"presented","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" case can be collapsed:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["-store.send(.destination(.presented(.tap)))","+store.send(\\.destination.tap)"],"syntax":"diff"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/IdentifiedAction","type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction","type":"reference"},{"text":" can be subscripted into:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff","code":["-store.send(.path(.element(id: 0, action: .tap)))","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].tap)"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/BindingAction","type":"reference"},{"text":"s can dynamically chain into a key path of state:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"diff","type":"codeListing","code":["-store.send(.binding(.set(\\.firstName, \"Blob\")))","+store.send(\\.binding.firstName, \"Blob\")"]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Together, these helpers can massively simplify asserting against nested actions:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["-store.send(","-  .path(","-    .element(","-      id: 0,","-      action: .destination(","-        .presented(","-          .sheet(","-            .binding(","-              .set(\\.password, \"blobisawesome\")","-            )","-          )","-        )","-      )","-    )","-  )","-)","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].destination.sheet.binding.password, \"blobisawesome\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff"}],"style":"tip","name":"Tip"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Overriding dependencies","anchor":"Overriding-dependencies"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Version 1.2 of ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"http:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-dependencies","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" introduced an","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"alternative syntax for referencing a dependency:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff","code":["-@Dependency(\\.apiClient) var apiClient","+@Dependency(APIClient.self) var apiClient"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The primary benefit of this syntax is that you do not need to define a dedicated computed property","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on ","type":"text"},{"code":"DependencyValues","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which saves a small amount of boilerplate.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is now a similar API for overriding dependencies on a reducer, "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Composa